                  <persName id="t18170917-64-person451">
                  THOMAS 
                  KNIGHT
               <interp inst="t18170917-64-person451" type="surname" value="KNIGHT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18170917-64-person451" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18170917-64-person451" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a <rs id="t18170917-64-viclabel310" type="occupation">farmer</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18170917-64-victim450 t18170917-64-viclabel310"></join> at Edmonton, the prisoner worked for me about two years ago. On the 26th of July, between twelve and one o'clock at night Burgess called me up; I went to the barn with him; it is kept locked; I found the outer leaf of the door propped up, and heard somebody getting up to the top loft - We went in and found the prisoner in the middle of the barn, and two bushels of wheat in a strange sack in the yard; it was not there the night before; it had been emptied out of my sacks. The prisoner said he was very sorry.</p>
               <p>JOHN BURGESS. I am servant to Mr. Knight, between twelve and one o'clock, I saw a light in the barn and called my master - We went there and saw the sack of wheat thrown out of the barn, and found the prisoner there.</p>
               <p>
